A renaissance of new ideas and cultural sharing had created a world filled with truly happy people.

When the rest of the world saw an opportunity to completely disconnect from the United States, they took it with gratitude.

A renaissance of new ideas and cultural sharing had created a world filled with truly happy people.

They kept saying that they were drawing lines in the sand, but there was no sand. It made no sense. When the rest of the world saw an opportunity to completely disconnect from the United States, they took it with gratitude.

Occasionally a tour group would get too close to the shores of America. They always came back, but with only half their intelligence left in tact. They would be filled with the most bizarre stories about how life in America had been. Many people were starving in the US, but not due to a lack of food. They had somehow convinced themselves that food was a conspiracy to control their minds and they simply stopped eating. Meanwhile, the rest of the world was living in great harmony. A renaissance of new ideas and cultural sharing had created a world filled with truly happy people. 

The United States was in shambles. They had enough money and resources to live for 1000 years in isolation, when they went into isolation. By the time the 50 years of isolation elapsed, much of the country was on fire and people were robbing each other with military style weapons for things that they didn't really need. The lack of competition with other nations had left the US with an identity problem. They solved this by taking on a new identity, as the most violent people in recorded history. T

They kept saying that they were drawing lines in the sand, but there was no sand. It made no sense. When the rest of the world saw an opportunity to completely disconnect from the United States, they took it with gratitude.

Occasionally a tour group would get too close to the shores of America. They always came back, but with only half their intelligence left in tact. They would be filled with the most bizarre stories about how life in America had been. Many people were starving in the US, but not due to a lack of food. They had somehow convinced themselves that food was a conspiracy to control their minds and they simply stopped eating. Meanwhile, the rest of the world was living in great harmony. A renaissance of new ideas and cultural sharing had created a world filled with truly happy people. 

The United States was in shambles. They had enough money and resources to live for 1000 years in isolation, when they went into isolation. By the time the 50 years of isolation elapsed, much of the country was on fire and people were robbing each other with military style weapons for things that they didn't really need. A renaissance of new ideas and cultural sharing had created a world filled with truly happy people. 

The United States was in shambles. They had enough money and resources to live for 1000 years in isolation, when they went into isolation. The lack of competition with other nations had left the US with an identity problem. They solved this by taking on a new identity, as the most violent people in recorded history. The contrast with what the rest of the world had become had been so dramatic, that Americans barely resembled people anymore. They were more like beasts.

Everyone stopped working at their jobs on the second day of isolation. Mostly, they just hunted and robbed one another, every day, for 50 years.
In the end, the United States was destroyed by a new type of bomb.
